caption: Beautiful Albanian restaurant tucked in Little Italy. Great ambience, great prices, great food. I went in looking for authentic Albanian food for the first time and came out speaking Albanian. Thats how authentic it is. 100% recommend.

Great place to bring friends and family... Or dine alone. Your choice. No judgement there. :)  Great mix of people having a great time and enjoying good south-eastern European food.  You can really just walk in here and ask for anything, and you'll like it.  Heavy on the meats, lots of dairy, and nice bean soup variations (to kill for).  I get the Pasul/fasul/etc (bean soup) with meat... I stay switching the meats up :)  Go and enjoy yourself. The others def are.

This is a cute little place with awesome food, though the people working there are not most friendliest. The food is awesome and the service is quick, the place is super clean. There is a restroom inside, finding parking around there is crazy, so park wherever you can and then just walk. I ordered the combo, I think it is the best option there if you want to taste the qebab, the suxhuk and qefte. The prices are reasonable for what is served, amazing deal.
